comments.author: nc50lc
comments.body: Quote from: Kingyouree on November 02, 2022, 04:18:38 PMhttps://postimg.cc/z3yfdrW6https://postimg.cc/RqpgBcWqhttps://postimg.cc/z3yfdrW6You posted the wrong image link for 3EkKxC1kDrJc4MvRqkXXyt7mpiA5UCLoRs.Since it's from your blockchain(dot)com wallet's "Trading Account", those transactions are generated by their system and it's custodial.I'm afraid that it's only their (blockchain com, not cash app) customer support that can solve the issue.Note: Only your 'Trading account' is custodial, your 'Private Key Wallet' and other accounts that you've created in the app's 'wallets & addresses' setting are non-custodial.
